Tic-Tac-Toe Game in Java

Overview
This is a simple console-based implementation of the classic Tic-Tac-Toe game written in Java. The game allows two players to take turns and place their marks ('X' or 'O')
on a 3x3 board. The player who succeeds in placing three of their marks in a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal row wins the game.

How to Play
1) The game starts with an empty 3x3 board.
2) Player 'X' makes the first move by entering the row and column number where they want to place their mark.
3) Player 'O' makes the next move in the same manner.
4) The game continues until a player wins by forming a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line with three of their marks or until the board is full resulting in a draw.

Features

1)Two-player gameplay
2)Input validation to ensure moves are made in empty spots
3)Detection of win conditions for rows, columns, and diagonals
4)Display of the game board after each move
